Body:
Description: Split from upgrade ticket 00442753
---------------
Upgraded NEA to 12.0 then ran the FS Create Schema job per standard post upgrade procedure.
Create Schema job hangs at final analysis task: 18.Data Migration > SQL script 1 of 3.

Confirmed in SSMS that query is running but it seems to run indefinitely.

Client killed the create schema job after 15 hours because the FSAA scan jobs were kicking off, on schedule.

 

When trying to run the FSAA scan and bulk import even though the Create Schema wasn't completed, the bulk import fails with the following errors (nor surprising):

 

Errors:

 

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess|Violation of PRIMARY KEY constraint 'PK_SA_FSAA_Trustees'. Cannot insert duplicate key in object 'dbo.SA_FSAA_Trustees'. The duplicate key value is (4, 3).

The statement has been terminated.

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess|Violation of PRIMARY KEY constraint 'PK_SA_FSAA_Trustees'. Cannot insert duplicate key in object 'dbo.SA_FSAA_Trustees'. The duplicate key value is (8, 2).

The statement has been terminated.

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess|Sequence contains no elements

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess|Violation of PRIMARY KEY constraint 'PK_SA_FSAA_Trustees'. Cannot insert duplicate key in object 'dbo.SA_FSAA_Trustees'. The duplicate key value is (6, 2).

The statement has been terminated.

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess|Ambiguous column name 'AccessID'.

Ambiguous column name 'ActivityID'.

Ambiguous column name 'DLPID'.

Fresh off the press from Development

 

There is a new log in 12.0 that may be helpful: the Coordination Service log.

This can be found in %SAINSTALLDIR%SADatabaseLogsCoordinationService on the NAA console.

 

I am not sure what these logs look like but probably worth grabbing for review.

What We've Learned Updated: create schema job still just hangs on the 18.Data Migration SQL script 1 of 3 step
the logs, even in debug, just hang at that point with no updates until the job is aborted

the job ran all weekend then timed out at 72 hours

client is running the FS_MigrateSchema job then will try the create schema job again

bulk import fails with errors (expected because create schema has to run first)
Next Steps Updated: asked client if FS_MigrateSchema job helped

Steps to Reproduce Updated: post 12.0 upgrade
run FS Create Schema job
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Tay Caliguiri, Eugene Johnson
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Tay Caliguiri

zoom meeting

 

after running the FS_MigrateSchema job completed, the FS Create Schema job was actually able to complete

it took 8 hours but finished seemingly without error

 

This completes the upgrade and this ticket but will need additional tickets for other issues:

 

UI latency of 15+ seconds post upgrade

FSAC scans fail because they need a bulk import

FSAC bulk import fails with Primary Key constraint
